The lattice model used here includes intra- and inter-strand site couplings and initial states prepared on one of the sites. For DNA lattices, parametrized according to atomistic simulations, in the absence of noise the energetic profile along complementary chains promotes fast population transfer for spatially separated sites due to long-range tunneling related to long-range coherences due to proper \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
